### Committees

Even as the legislative body itself was in turmoil, the committees, the bureaucratic organs of Congress, continued their work, a testament to the enduring, if sometimes Sisyphean, nature of governance.

#### Senate

*   Alter and Improve Senate Chamber (Select)
*   Amendments to the Constitution (Select)
*   [Audit and Control the Contingent Expenses of the Senate](/United_States_Senate_Committee_to_Audit_and_Control_the_Contingent_Expenses_of_the_Senate) (Chairman: [Andrew Johnson](/Andrew_Johnson))
*   Banks of the District of Columbia (Select)
*   Circulation of Bank Notes in the District of Columbia (Select)
*   [Claims](/United_States_Senate_Committee_on_Claims) (Chairman: [Alfred Iverson Jr.](/Alfred_Iverson_Jr.))
*   [Commerce](/United_States_Senate_Committee_on_Commerce) (Chairman: [Clement Claiborne Clay](/Clement_Claiborne_Clay))
*   Comptroller William Medill (Select)
*   Distributing Public Revenue Among the States (Select)
*   [District of Columbia](/United_States_Senate_Committee_on_the_District_of_Columbia) (Chairman: [Albert G. Brown](/Albert_G._Brown))
*   Duties of Imports (Select)
*   [Finance](/United_States_Senate_Committee_on_Finance) (Chairman: [Robert M. T. Hunter](/Robert_M._T._Hunter))
*   [Foreign Relations](/United_States_Senate_Committee_on_Foreign_Relations) (Chairman: [James M. Mason](/James_M._Mason))
*   French Spoliations (Select)
*   Harpers Ferry Invasion (Select), a committee undoubtedly formed in the wake of [John Brown's](/John_Brown_(abolitionist)) violent raid, reflecting the immediate legislative response to national crises.
*   [Indian Affairs](/United_States_Senate_Committee_on_Indian_Affairs) (Chairman: [William K. Sebastian](/William_K._Sebastian))
*   [Judiciary](/United_States_Senate_Committee_on_the_Judiciary) (Chairman: [James A. Bayard Jr.](/James_A._Bayard_Jr.))
*   Memorial of Houmas Lands Settlers (Select)
*   [Military Affairs](/United_States_Senate_Committee_on_Military_Affairs) (Chairman: [Jefferson Davis](/Jefferson_Davis)), a committee whose chairman would soon lead an opposing army. The irony is palpable.
*   [Naval Affairs](/United_States_Senate_Committee_on_Naval_Affairs) (Chairman: [Stephen Mallory](/Stephen_Mallory)), another chairman who would soon oversee the Confederate Navy.
*   Ordnance and War Ships (Select), a prescient committee given the impending conflict.
*   Pacific Railroad (Select), looking to the future even as the present crumbled.
*   [Patents and the Patent Office](/United_States_Senate_Committee_on_Patents_and_the_Patent_Office) (Chairman: [William Bigler](/William_Bigler))
